"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752810","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-20","<p>We do not hold any data on the effect of the benefit cap on the health and well-being of children.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Government believes that encouraging households to move into work through the benefit cap will help to increase the household’s income and help to improve their wellbeing:</p><p> </p><p>Research shows that for adults without work, re-employment leads to improvement in health and wellbeing, whereas further unemployment leads to deterioration. Research also shows that it is not in the best interests of children to live in workless households. For example, children in households where neither parent is in work are much more likely to have challenging behaviour at age 5 than children in households where both parents are in paid employment.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-20T08:00:04.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752810/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752810/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752810/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-17","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of the benefit cap on the health and well-being of children.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","5296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752811","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-21","<p>Ofgem is considering options to protect vulnerable consumers and has yet to announce a formal proposal. Alongside this Ofgem has announced a package of measures to help consumers move away from poor value tariffs.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-21T12:57:27.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752811/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752811/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752811/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-17","Energy: Wrexham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent estimate he has made of the number and proportion of people in Wrexham constituency who will be covered by the Government's latest proposals to safeguard customers on the poorest value energy tariff.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","5272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752812","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-20","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-20T15:11:31.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752812/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752812/answer","PQ5273 v.02.pdf","PQ5273 v.02.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ5273","UKSA Response to PQ5273","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752812/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-17","Public Sector: Wrexham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many and what proportion of people in Wrexham constituency worked in the public sector in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","5273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752813","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-20","<p>All Assessment Centre buildings [operated by Independent Assessment Services (an Atos company), Capita, and the Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (CHDA)] are compliant with the Equality Act 2010 and are wheelchair accessible.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The assessment providers are required to ensure that the needs of all claimants are considered, including proximity to public transport routes and access to suitable parking. Before attending an assessment, claimants are given the opportunity to alert the assessment provider to any additional requirements they may have. The providers will endeavour to meet any reasonable requests.</p><p> </p><p>If a claimant is unable to travel to, or access an Assessment Centre as a result of their health condition or impairment, a home visit may be offered.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","5252 ; 5253","2017-07-20T12:53:59.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752813/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752813/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752813/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-17","Social Security Benefits: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many health and disability assessment centres are not wheelchair-accessible.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","5251"
