"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752982","Department for International Development","false","2017-07-20","<p>Our assessment is that insecticide and drug resistance pose a real threat to the recent progress seen on malaria. This is why DFID is a leading global funder of efforts to tackle malaria, through research funding, bilateral treatment and control programmes and our funding to multilateral institutions such as the Global Fund. This support includes developing new drugs and new insecticides, in response to current levels of insecticide resistance. We also support drug management programmes that decrease the chances of resistance building up, and other measures of tackling malaria, such as the use of bednets.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-07-20T16:27:24.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752982/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752982/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-07-17","Developing Countries: Malaria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the implications of emerging resistance to insecticides and drugs for the level of international financing required to eliminate malaria.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","5483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752983","Department for International Development","false","2017-07-20","<p>The UK spent £30.2 million on education programmes in 2016/17 which represents around 10% of DFID's bilateral support to Nigeria.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-07-20T16:23:47.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752983/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752983/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752983/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-07-17","Nigeria: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of the Government's international aid budget is spent on education in Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","5441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752984","Department for International Development","false","2017-07-20","<p>By helping the world’s poorest women access modern contraception, we will prevent an estimated 6 million unintended pregnancies and 3 million abortions on average each year.</p><p>Family planning reduces, but on its own does not eliminate, the backstreet abortions that kill women. So, where this is not against local law, the UK will consider supporting access to safe abortion in the world’s poorest countries. UK aid cannot be used to fund illegal services.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","5618 ; 5619 ; 5620 ; 5621","2017-07-20T16:23:00.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752984/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752984/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-07-17","Developing Countries: Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what information her Department holds on the number of abortions which have been carried out as a result of her Department's spending in developing countries from 2011 to 2016.","false","Biography information for Ian Paisley","North Antrim","Ian Paisley","5606"
