"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752102","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>On 26 May HMRC exchanged on the agreement for lease for New Waverley Place. In line with purdah guidance, HMRC sought and followed Cabinet Office advice before making this commitment.</p><p> </p><p>The decision to move HMRC jobs to the Edinburgh regional centre was announced in November 2015. No decisions were made on moving jobs to the Edinburgh Regional Centre during purdah.</p><p> </p><p>As part of wider business planning, meetings to discuss the moves have taken place regularly since November 2015.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","5047 ; 5049","2017-07-19T14:52:44.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752102/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752102/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-14","Revenue and Customs: Edinburgh","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what decisions were taken during the purdah period before the 2017 General Election on moving HM Revenue and Customs jobs to Waverley Gate in Edinburgh.","false","Biography information for Hannah Bardell","Livingston","Hannah Bardell","5048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752103","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-19T09:35:40.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752103/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752103/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752103/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Lone Parents: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many families in Scotland are lone parent families with one or more children under the age of two and subject to the benefit cap.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","5068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752104","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>We do not hold any data on the effect of the benefit cap on food insecurity.</p><p> </p><p>The lower cap is still the equivalent of gross family earnings of £25k, and £29k in London. Where claimants need further financial support, Local Authorities can provide additional support through the use of Discretionary Housing Payments.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-19T09:37:20.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752104/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752104/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the benefit cap on food insecurity.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","5069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752105","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-19T16:19:28.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752105/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752105/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752105/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Department for Work and Pensions: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much money his Department has spent on legal fees in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","5070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752106","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>We do not hold any data on the number of public sector workers subject to the benefit cap. Households are exempt if entitled to Working Tax Credit, (essentially, lone parents working 16 hours per week and couples working 24 hours per week between them where one partner works at least 16 hours per week) or in Universal Credit if earning £520 per month.</p><p> </p><p>Households can be exempt from the cap if they are claiming WTC and the most recent official statistics show that</p><p> </p><ul><li><strong>134,000</strong> households in Great Britain have been capped since April 2013</li><li><strong>68,000</strong> households are no longer subject to cap and<strong> 29,000 of these (43%) </strong>are exempt due to working tax credit indicating they <strong>have found work.</strong></li></ul>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-19T09:28:03.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752106/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752106/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752106/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Social Security Benefits: Public Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make an estimate of the number of benefit claimants subject to the household benefit cap who are public sector workers subject to the one per cent pay cap.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","5071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752107","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-20","<p>We regularly raise concerns with the Turkish authorities over the situation of those who – like Nuriye Gulmen and Semih Ozakca – have been dismissed or detained under the State of Emergency following last year’s attempted coup. We therefore share Ms Kofler’s concerns. We have urged the Turkish authorities to respect international standards, including regarding the presumption of innocence, as well as freedom of expression and assembly.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-20T07:47:56.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752107/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752107/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752107/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-14","Turkey: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the statement by Bärbel Kofler, the Federal Government Commissioner for Human Rights Policy and Humanitarian Aid at the Federal Foreign Office in Germany, of 13 June 2017, on the arrest and detention of Nuriye Gülmen and Semih Özakça.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","5063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752108","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Secretary of State met with the Trussell Trust in Dacorum on 7th of July, a range of topics were discussed including Universal Credit. Universal Credit has been rolled out everywhere and is available in all Jobcentres.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-19T16:31:40.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752108/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752108/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752108/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he has had with the Trussell Trust on recent trends in demand for foodbanks in areas where universal credit (a) has and (b) has not been rolled out; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752109","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>We are intending to publish further data on payment timeliness in due course, but based on our latest internal data, for week ending 19 June, we estimate that some 80% of cases were paid in full at the end of the first assessment period.</p><p>For the 20% of cases who were not paid in full we estimate around a third have not signed up to their claimant commitment so cannot be paid until they have. The other two thirds have an outstanding verification issue, such as providing bank statements, evidence of childcare costs, or proof of rent. Many of these claimants receive a part-payment where elements of the claim have been verified.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-19T13:10:50.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752109/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752109/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752109/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of universal credit applicants wait more than (a) six and (b) 10 weeks after making their claim before they receive any income.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752110","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>I refer the Honourable Member to the answer I gave on 18 July 2017 to questions 4800 and 4801.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","5055","2017-07-19T09:19:01.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752110/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752110/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752110/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department has taken to improve the accuracy of the real time information it receives from HM Revenue and Customs to calculate awards of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752111","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>We have no plans to make any further cuts to disability benefits beyond those already legislated for.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-19T10:24:59.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752111/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752111/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752111/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Social Security Benefits: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make it his Department's policy to make no further cuts to disability benefits in the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752112","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>I refer the Honourable Member to the answer I gave on 18 July 2017 to questions 4800 and 4801.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","5044","2017-07-19T09:19:02.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752112/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752112/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752112/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of the accuracy of the income data supplied through real time information by HM Revenue and Customs to calculate awards of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752113","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-24","<p>In 2018 it is planned that claimants will be provided with the ability to book and manage their own appointments online through Universal Credit Full Service.</p><p> </p><p>There are currently no plans to introduce an online appointment booking system for claimants in receipt of benefits that are planned to migrate over to Universal Credit Full Service from July 2019 onwards.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-24T12:48:54.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752113/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752113/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752113/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Jobcentres: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to introduce online booking for jobcentre appointments.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","5056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752114","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-24","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is doing detailed work with departments to prepared for the upcoming negotiations by understanding the risks and opportunities of leaving the EU and coordinating planning. Staff within the DCMS EU Team lead on providing advice to Ministers on EU Exit and related issues. Members of staff across the Department also provide advice and analyses on EU Exit issues as required. Given the interactions between EU exit work and the Department's other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-24T08:57:41.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752114/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752114/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752114/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-14","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many staff in her Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752115","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-21","<p>The Ministry of Defence has allocated five staff to deal exclusively with work arising from the UK's decision to leave the European Union so far as it affects Defence. These officials draw on the expertise of a wide range of colleagues from across the Ministry of Defence who undertake work relating to the UK's withdrawal from the European Union, in addition to their normal duties.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-21T14:09:35.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752115/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752115/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752115/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-14","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752116","Department for Education","false","2017-07-24","<p>The department has four members of staff working full time on co-ordinating and contributing to cross-department and cross-government work on EU exit. These staff are supported by a range of civil servants across the department who lead on specific policy areas and whose work includes, but is not limited to EU exit work.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-07-24T14:19:30.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752116/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752116/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752116/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-14","Department for Education: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many staff in her Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752117","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-24","<p>Exit is an all-of-government operation. The Department for Exiting the European Union is doing detailed work with departments to prepare for the upcoming negotiations by understanding the risks and opportunities of leaving the EU and coordinating planning.</p><p>Staff within the EU Exit Programme in Defra lead on providing advice to Ministers on EU Exit and exit-related issues and members of staff across the Department also provide advice and analysis on EU Exit issues as required.</p><p>Given the interactions between EU exit work and the Department’s other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-07-24T10:25:31.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752117/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752117/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752117/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-14","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752118","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-24","<p>​The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO), along with other Government Departments, is working with the Department for Exiting the EU (DExEU) to support the UK's exit from the EU. Within the FCO, the Europe Directorate provides advice to FCO Ministers on EU-related issues. This may sometimes include EU exit-related issues. There are some staff members in the FCO's Europe Directorate who work predominantly on the UK's exit from the EU. Staff in other London Directorates, as well as our diplomatic missions around the world, also on occasion work on EU-related issues and this may involve work related to the UK's exit from the EU. Therefore it is not possible to give precise figures.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-24T14:39:15.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752118/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752118/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752118/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-14","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752119","Department of Health","false","2017-07-21","<p>The work of the Department in ensuring a smooth and orderly exit from the European Union is coordinated by a central team within the Global and Public Health Directorate. All affected policy teams within the Department are involved with this work and assessing the implications of the United Kingdom leaving the EU on their area.</p><p> </p><p>The resources available are kept under constant review and the Department is equipping itself with the resources it needs to get the best deal for the UK.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-07-21T12:34:31.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752119/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752119/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752119/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-14","Department of Health: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752120","Home Office","false","2017-07-24","<p>The UK’s exit from the EU is a cross-government operation. The Department for Exiting the European Union is doing detailed work with departments to prepare for the upcoming negotiations by understanding the risks and opportunities of leaving the EU and coordinating planning.</p><p> </p><p>Staff within the Home Office Europe Directorate and the Border Immigration and Citizenship System Policy and Strategy Group lead on providing advice to Ministers on EU exit and exit related issues. Members of staff across the Department also provide advice and analysis on EU exit issues as required.</p><p> </p><p>Given the interactions between EU exit work and the Department’s other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure on how many staff in the Home Office have responsibilities relating to exiting the EU.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2017-07-24T15:59:58.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752120/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752120/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-14","Home Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many staff in her Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752121","Department for International Development","false","2017-07-24","<p>Exit is an all-of-government operation. The Department for Exiting the European Union is doing detailed work with departments to prepare for the upcoming negotiations by understanding the risks and opportunities of leaving the EU and coordinating planning.</p><p>Staff within the DFID Europe Department and DFID Trade for Development team based in the Department for International Trade, lead on providing advice to Ministers on EU Exit and exit-related issues.</p><p>Members of staff across the Department also provide advice and analysis on EU Exit issues as required.</p><p>Given the interactions between EU Exit work and the Department’s other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-07-24T12:48:37.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752121/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752121/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-07-14","Department for International Development: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many staff in her Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752122","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-24","<p>The whole of Government is preparing for the UK to make an orderly and successful exit from the European Union. The Department for Exiting the European Union, is doing detailed work with departments to prepare for the upcoming negotiations, by understanding the risks and opportunities of leaving the EU and coordinating planning.</p><p> </p><p>Staff within DIT’s Trade Policy Group lead on providing advice to Ministers on EU Exit and exit-related trade issues.</p><p> </p><p>Members of staff across the Department also provide advice and analysis on EU Exit issues as required.</p><p> </p><p>Given the interactions between EU exit work and the Department’s other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-07-24T14:52:13.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752122/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752122/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752122/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-14","Department for International Trade: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752123","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-07-24","<p>Staff within the Ministry of Justice’s EU exit policy team lead on providing advice to Ministers on EU exit and exit-related issues. Members of staff across the Department also provide advice and analysis on EU exit issues as required. Given the interactions between EU exit work and the Department’s other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure.</p><p> </p><p>Exit is an all-of-Government operation. The Department for exiting the European Union is doing detailed work with Departments to prepare for the upcoming negotiations by understanding the risks and opportunities of leaving the EU and coordinating planning.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-07-24T15:39:06.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752123/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752123/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752123/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-07-14","Ministry of Justice: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752124","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-19","<p>Exit is an all-of-government operation. The Department for Exiting the European Union is undertaking detailed work with departments to prepare for the upcoming negotiations by understanding the risks and opportunities of leaving the EU and coordinating planning.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Staff in my Department continue to work closely with officials in the Department for Exiting the European Union. Indeed, a large contingent of Cabinet Office staff formed the basis of the new Department’s workforce when it was created last year.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Members of staff across the Department also provide advice and analysis on EU Exit issues as required.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>But given the interactions between EU exit work and the Department’s other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-07-19T15:33:19.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752124/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752124/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752124/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-14","Cabinet Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752125","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-14","<p>I refer the honourable member to my answer given on 19 th July to PQ 5019.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-11-14T10:31:12.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752125/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752125/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752125/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-14","Cabinet Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752126","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-20","<p>The Department’s Europe Directorate and EU Exit and International Trade directorate employ dedicated teams of full-time officials who work on negotiations and the domestic consequences of leaving the EU, as well as our ongoing engagement with the EU whilst we are still members. Officials in other teams in the Department also carry out EU exit-related work as part of their broader responsibilities. The Department will continue to ensure there is an appropriate level of resource to deliver its EU exit work.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-20T14:18:57.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752126/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752126/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752126/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-14","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752127","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-24","<p>EU exit is an all-of-Government operation. The Department for Exiting the European Union is doing detailed work with departments to prepare for the upcoming negotiations by understanding the risks and opportunities of leaving the EU and coordinating planning. Within the Department for Communities and Local Government, staff within the EU Exit Team lead on providing advice to Ministers on EU exit and exit-related issues. Members of staff across the Department also provide advice and analysis on EU Exit issues as required. Given the interactions between EU exit work and the Department's other priorities, it would not be possible to give an accurate figure.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2017-07-24T15:03:06.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752127/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752127/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752127/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-14","Department for Communities and Local Government: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many staff in his Department have responsibilities which relate to preparations for the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","5010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752128","Department of Health","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Department does not hold information on the number of people who had an operation to amputate a limb since 2010.</p><p> </p><p>NHS Digital regularly collects publically available information on the number of finished episodes of care involving amputation, however one person may have multiple episodes of such care.</p><p> </p><p>Rehabilitation involves a specialised multi-disciplinary team, which includes a psychologist, and counselling should be made available to any person with limb loss, but we do not collect information on the level of psychological support offered in rehabilitation.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-07-19T10:46:31.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752128/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752128/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752128/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-14","Orthopaedics: Rehabilitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 10 July 2017 to Question 3123, what information in any format his Department holds on the number of people in England who had an operation to amputate a limb since 2010; and what psychological support is available to such people during their rehabilitation.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","5041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752129","Department of Health","false","2017-07-19","<p>This data is not collected in the format requested. NHS England directly commissions specialised services for mental health and eating disorders; including those for National Health Service services in the independent sector. Other services for eating disorders and mental health services are commissioned by clinical commissioning groups.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-07-19T10:38:37.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752129/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752129/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752129/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-14","NHS: Private Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 3 July 2017 to Question 1736, whether his Department holds any information on how much the NHS has paid private healthcare companies for the provision of (a) eating disorder and (b) mental health services since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","5004"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752130","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-20","<p>The number and average value of houses purchased in the Lichfield constituency broken down by HS2 scheme/arrangement is as follows.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Scheme/Arrangement</p></td><td><p>Number of properties purchased</p></td><td><p>Average value of each purchase</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Exceptional Hardship Scheme*</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>£549,235</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Need to Sell</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>£550,500</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Voluntary Purchase</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>£406,625</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Statutory Blight</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>£829,636</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Atypical arrangements</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>£406,625</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*In May 2016 the Exceptional Hardship Scheme was withdrawn for the Phase 2a section of HS2 when the Need to Sell scheme was confirmed for this part of the route<strong> </strong></p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-20T13:57:19.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752130/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752130/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752130/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-14","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Lichfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many houses in Lichfield constituency have been purchased by (a) the High Speed 2 Exceptional Hardship Scheme and (b) other related schemes since each such scheme was launched; and what the average cost has been of purchases under each such scheme.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","5009"
