"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752134","Department for Education","false","2017-07-24","<p>We are providing an additional £1.3 billion for schools across 2018-19 and 2019-20 to support the introduction of the national funding formula from April next year. Along with the funding we had already committed for schools at the 2015 Spending Review, this will mean the core schools budget rises from just under £41 billion in 2017-18 to £43.5 billion by 2020. The additional investment means that, over the next two years, we will be able to provide for a 0.5% a year per pupil increase for every school. Full details of the arrangements are set out at:<br> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/justine-greening-statement-to-parliament-on-school-funding" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/justine-greening-statement-to-parliament-on-school-funding</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","5036","2017-07-24T17:39:06.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752134/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752134/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752134/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-14","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will ensure that the Government increases its funding for local authorities sufficiently to ensure that no school will receive a cut in funding as a result of the imposition of the national funding formula.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","5037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752135","Department for Education","false","2017-07-24","<p>We are providing an additional £1.3 billion for schools across 2018-19 and 2019-20 to support the introduction of the national funding formula from April next year. Along with the funding we had already committed for schools at the 2015 Spending Review, this will mean the core schools budget rises from just under £41 billion in 2017-18 to £43.5 billion by 2020. The additional investment means that, over the next two years, we will be able to provide for a 0.5% a year per pupil increase for every school. Full details of the arrangements are set out at:<br> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/justine-greening-statement-to-parliament-on-school-funding" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/justine-greening-statement-to-parliament-on-school-funding</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","5037","2017-07-24T17:39:06.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752135/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752135/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752135/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-14","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will estimate the cost to the public purse of ensuring that no school receives a reduction in funding as a result of the national funding formula in the 2018-19 financial year.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","5036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752136","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Childcare ITF is chaired by the Education Secretary and was established to drive delivery of a coherent and effective government-wide childcare offer to support parents in work. To protect the integrity of the policy making process, we do not not publish details of when Implementation Taskforces met or what they discussed.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-19T12:40:07.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752136/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752136/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752136/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-14","Childcare Implementation Taskforce","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many times the childcare implementation taskforce has met since its establishment; what were the dates on which it met; and who attended each meeting.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","4999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752137","Department for Education","false","2017-07-19","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to his previous question number 3689, which was answered on 12 July:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-07/3689/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-07/3689/</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li><p> </p></li></ul>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-07-19T15:54:58.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752137/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752137/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752137/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-14","Sixth Form Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 30 June 2017 to Question 1097, how much funding was allocated to 16-to-19 education in (a) 2014-15 and (b) 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","5005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752138","Department for Education","false","2017-07-24","<p>The Department for Education is concluding the procurement of the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund at present. The procurement has been designed to be responsive to bidders’ proposals and, as such, the Department has not made ‘top-down’ estimates of numbers to receive training in 2017-18.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-24T14:21:27.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752138/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752138/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752138/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-14","Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the number of teachers and school leaders to receive training through the Teaching and Leadership Fund in 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","5012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752139","Department for Education","false","2017-07-24","<p>The Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund is the subject of an open procurement under the 2015 Public Procurement Regulations. At present, the Department for Education is concluding this procurement. Details of the successful bidders will be released in due course.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-24T14:22:55.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752139/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752139/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752139/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-14","Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which organisations have been selected to take part in the Teaching and Leadership Fund.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","5013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752140","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>HMRC publishes this information in the Creative Industries Statistics here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/creative-industries-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/creative-industries-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>The next release of these statistics, including the latest data for 2014-15, 2015-16 and 2016-17, will be published on 20 July 2017.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-19T14:07:24.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752140/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752140/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752140/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-14","Television: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many companies received high-end TV tax relief in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","5053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752141","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Government does not hold information on the number of people that would pay Capital Gains Tax on their main residence if there were not an exemption, as taxpayers are not usually required to submit a Capital Gains Tax return when they sell their main home.</p><p> </p><p>The Government publishes an estimate of the total cost of the tax relief on the only or main residence. This is available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/579720/Dec_16_Main_Reliefs_Final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/579720/Dec_16_Main_Reliefs_Final.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-19T13:44:13.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752141/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752141/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752141/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-14","Capital Gains Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received capital gains tax exemption on the disposal of their only or main residence in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","5002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752142","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>HMRC publishes official statistics on the number of companies claiming the Patent Box relief, on an annual basis. The statistics are available in the “<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/patent-box-reliefs-statistics" target="_blank">Patent box statistics</a>” publication which shows provisional estimates of 700 companies claiming Patent Box relief for 2013-14.</p><p> </p><p>The next release of these statistics, including the latest data for 2013-14 and 2014-15 will be published in mid-September.</p><p>Official figures for 2015-16 and 2016-17 will be published in future years because companies, have up to 2 years after the end of the accounting period in which to claim the Patent Box relief.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-19T14:42:35.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752142/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752142/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752142/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-14","Patents: Corporation Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received corporation tax relief on patent boxes in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16 and (c) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","5003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752143","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-19","<p>​We routinely update our guidance to British businesses on the Overseas Business Risk website. Our guidance about Israel was last refreshed in September 2016.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-07-19T11:42:30.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752143/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752143/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-14","Israeli Settlements: Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when his Department last updated its guidance for UK companies who want to trade with illegal settlements in the Palestinian Occupied Territories.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","5000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752144","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-19","<p>Since November 2014, 61 acres of invasive acacia have been removed from the Special Area of Conservation and land managed by the Ministry of Defence on Cape Pyla. The annual breakdown is as follows:</p><p>17 acres removed in 2014</p><p>22 acres removed in 2015</p><p>22 acres completed in 2016[1]</p><p>Invasive acacia has also been removed from other Special Areas of Conservation on land managed by the Ministry of Defence elsewhere in the Sovereign Base Areas of Akrotiri and Dhekelia during 2016 and 2017.</p><p> </p><p>[1] Work began during the Christmas period in 2015 and completed in the New Year of 2016</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-19T14:54:27.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752144/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752144/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752144/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-14","Cyprus: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what area of invasive Australian acacia tree has been removed from his Department's land, the Cape Pyla, in the Cyprus sovereign base area of Dhekelia in (a) 2014, (b) 2015, (c) 2016 and (d) 2017.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","5001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752145","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-20","<p>Table 1 below shows the number of Personal Independence Payment (PIP) initial decisions and Mandatory Reconsideration decisions where the award was changed by year since the introduction of PIP in the Parliamentary Constituency of Blaenau Gwent.</p><p> </p><p><em>Table 1 – Number of Initial decisions and Mandatory Reconsiderations decisions where the award changed by year of decision.</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year of Initial Decision</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>2017 (to April)</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of Initial decisions for PIP (Exc. Withdrawn cases)</p></td><td><p>50</p></td><td><p>1,280</p></td><td><p>1,370</p></td><td><p>1,510</p></td><td><p>990</p></td><td><p>5,180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Year of Mandatory Reconsideration</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>2017 (to April)</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number of Awards Changed at Mandatory Reconsideration</p></td><td><p>#</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>70</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>180</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Tribunal Statistics, including appeal outcomes are published by the Ministry of Justice and so we will not be able to provide consistent regional breakdown of these statistics for Blaenau Gwent.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-20T15:46:29.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752145/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752145/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Personal Independence Payment: Blaenau Gwent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of constituents in Blaenau Gwent have had their personal independence payments overturned as a result of (a) mandatory reconsideration and (b) an appeal hearing in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","5017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752146","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-20","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply<strong>.</strong></p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-20T15:18:10.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752146/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752146/answer","PQ5016 v.02.pdf","PQ5016 v.02.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ5016","UKSA Response to PQ5016","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752146/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-14","Public Sector: Blaenau Gwent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what information his Department holds on the number and proportion of constituents in Blaenau Gwent who worked in the public sector in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","5016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752147","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>National statistics on the number of children in relative low income are set out in the annual &quot;Households Below Average Income&quot; publication. The number and proportion of children in relative low income is not available at local authority or constituency level in this publication because the survey sample sizes are too small to support the production of robust estimates at this geography.</p><p> </p><p>Latest 3-year estimates for Wales of the proportion of children in low income are available in Table 4.16ts in the file “4_children_timeseries_risk” from this link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/599136/hbai-2015-2016-supporting-ods-files.zip" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/599136/hbai-2015-2016-supporting-ods-files.zip</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-19T15:02:44.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752147/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752147/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752147/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what information his Department has on the number and proportion of children living in poverty in Blaenau Gwent in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","5015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752148","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-20","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-20T15:44:07.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752148/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752148/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Disability Living Allowance: Blaenau Gwent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of constituents in Blaenau Gwent who were categorised as lifelong recipients of disability living allowance were subsequently judged as ineligible for personal independence payments in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","5014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752149","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Foreign Secretary has not held discussions with the Government of Montserrat on its public register of beneficial ownership.</p><p>FCO officials remain in regular contact with the Government of Montserrat over its plans for the register. Montserrat officials are finalising for the consideration of the Montserrat Cabinet draft legislation which will underpin the establishment of a public register. It will then be for the Cabinet to determine the timetable for introducing the Bill to the Legislative Assembly.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-19T14:16:59.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752149/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752149/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752149/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-14","Montserrat: Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with representatives of the Montserrat Government on a public register of beneficial ownership; and what the timetable is for that territory's public register of beneficial ownership to be set up.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","5039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752150","Department for Education","false","2017-07-19","<p>My Rt hon. Friend the Secretary of State has had no such meetings.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-07-19T15:21:55.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752150/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752150/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-14","Open University: Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether she has had any discussions with the Open University on its use of a restricted countries list in its application process.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","5040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752151","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Chancellor of the Exchequer announced at the Autumn Statement in November 2016 that the tax relief will include permanent exhibitions.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2017-07-19T10:37:50.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752151/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752151/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-14","Museums and Galleries: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on the extension of museums and galleries tax relief to permanent exhibitions.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","5035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752152","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-19","<p>​The British Government has consistently encouraged Turkey to work towards the full protection of human rights, through implementation of its international human rights obligations. Ministers monitor the situation closely, and the Prime Minister raised human rights with President Erdogan at the G20 summit on 8 July. The FCO also provides direct support to a number of Turkish civil society organisations working to protect and promote fundamental freedoms.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-19T14:14:12.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752152/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752152/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-14","Turkey: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of whether Turkey is meeting its international human rights obligations.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","5054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752153","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>Autumn Statement 2016 announced that the Museums and Galleries Tax Relief would be extended to include permanent exhibitions.</p><p> </p><p>This tax relief will provide support to museums and galleries to encourage them to develop creative new exhibitions and display their collections to a wider audience.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-19T14:38:45.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752153/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752153/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-14","Museums and Galleries: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has plans to extend museums and galleries tax relief to permanent exhibitions.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","5038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752154","Department of Health","false","2017-07-19","<p>Whilst 79% of inspected care services are good or outstanding there is more to do to address variation. This is why we introduced tougher inspections of care services and provided an additional £2 billion to the sector. The Department is also working with organisations from across the adult social care sector to implement Quality Matters – a commitment to improving quality.</p><p> </p><p>The Government announced that we will be consulting on the future of social care. The consultation will set out options to improve the social care system to put it on a more secure financial footing and address issues related to the quality of care and variation in practice.</p><p> </p><p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC) makes sure adult social care providers meet fundamental standards of quality and safety. The CQC reports that 75% of inspected providers are rated as good for ‘safety’.</p><p>The CQC can take action if it identifies aspects of care which need to improve. The CQC can: issue requirement notices or warning notices to set out what improvements must be made and by when; make changes to a care provider's registration to limit what they may do; place a provider in special measures; and, issue cautions, fines or prosecute cases where people are harmed or placed in danger of harm.</p><p> </p><p>The CQC reports that 76% of inspected providers are rated as outstanding or good for ‘well-led’. The Department is working closely with our delivery partners, Skills for Care, to improve the level of skills of the adult social care workforce which includes supporting the development of leadership at all levels. The Skills for Care Leadership programme equips leaders and managers at all levels to positively embrace service transformation as part of an integrated, whole-system view of person-centred care.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","5058 ; 5060 ; 5073","2017-07-19T16:01:50.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752154/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752154/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-14","Care Homes: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the Care Quality Commission's finding that safety is one of the key areas where residential care homes are struggling to improve; and what steps he plans to take to address that finding.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","5059"
