"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752156","Department of Health","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Care Act 2014 placed a duty on local authorities in England to promote a diverse, sustainable, high quality market of care and support providers for people in their local area.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has published statutory guidance to support local authorities in their market shaping duties.</p><p>To improve the quality of adult social care, the Government has introduced a tough system of Care Quality Commission ratings, new qualifications for care workers and new standards to ensure that everyone receives the highest quality support.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-07-19T10:45:22.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752156/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752156/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-14","Care Homes: Nottingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure that older people can access high-quality residential care in Nottingham.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","5057"
