"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752159","Home Office","false","2017-07-24","<p>The 2015 Spending Review protected overall police spending in real terms, and the 2017/18 police funding settlement maintained that protection.</p><p>It is a local decision for Police and Crime Commissioners, working with Chief Constables, to determine the composition and size of their workforce.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-24T12:22:05.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752159/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752159/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-14","Metropolitan Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she plans to reduce the number of police officers in the Metropolitan Police Force during the course of the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","4995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752160","Home Office","false","2017-07-24","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes data on the number of officers primarily employed in Neighbourhood Policing/Safer Neighbourhood roles by police force area.</p><p> </p><p>The number of full time equivalent police officers in the Metropolitan Police,</p><p>primarily employed in Neighbourhood Policing/Safer Neighbourhood roles, can be found in the data tables published alongside the annual ‘Police workforce, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins, which can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales</a></p><p> </p><p>Data as at 31 March 2016 can be found in Table F4 of the police workforce statistics published in July 2016: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/544954/police-workforce-tabs-jul16.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/544954/police-workforce-tabs-jul16.ods</a></p><p> </p><p>Previous data were collected under a different framework, with different definitions. Therefore, data prior to 31 March 2015 are not directly comparable with later years. Although some functions may appear to be similar between the two, there are often differences in definitions, and so any attempts to compare across the two frameworks should be done with caution. Data under the old framework have been published since 2012, and can be found in the supplementary data tables of the relevant police workforce publications via the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales</a></p><p> </p><p>Officers with multiple responsibilities or designations are recorded under their primary function. The data do not therefore provide a complete picture of all officers assigned to neighbourhood policing functions. A more reliable measure is the number of officers employed in ‘Local policing’ roles, which includes both neighbourhood and response functions. This measure is available for 2015 and 2016, but not for previous years where a different framework was used.</p><p> </p><p>Any comparisons at force level should be made with care due to collaboration arrangements between forces for particular functions. Additionally, police functions data are often affected by re-structuring within police forces. Therefore comparisons over time for specific functions should be made with care.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-24T12:24:43.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752160/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752160/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-14","Metropolitan Police: Safer Neighbourhood Teams","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many metropolitan police officers there were serving in Greater London in Safer Neighbourhood Teams in (a) 2011 and (b) 2016.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","4997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752161","Home Office","false","2017-07-24","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes police workforce data annually on the number of officers primarily employed in Counter Terrorism/Special Branch roles as part of the <em>Police workforce, England and Wales </em>statistical bulletin. This can be accessed at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Data as at 31 March 2016 can be found in Table F4 of the police workforce statistics published in July 2016 at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/544954/police-workforce-tabs-jul16.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/544954/police-workforce-tabs-jul16.ods</a> and record that 3,888 officers were designated as primarily involved in counter-terrorism or Special Branch.</p><p> </p><p>This figure does not include all officers supporting counter-terrorism work and excludes many of those posts funded separately by the Counter-Terrorism Policing Grant and those in some national counter-terrorism functions. For reasons of national security, we do not publish the number or location of posts funded by the Counter-Terrorism Policing Grant. The published figures do not, therefore, reflect the total number of officers assigned to counter-terrorism policing.</p><p> </p><p>Previous data were collected under a different framework, with different definitions. Therefore, data prior to 31 March 2015 are not directly comparable with later years. Although some functions may appear to be similar between the two frameworks, there are often differences in definitions, and so any attempts to compare across the two should be done with caution. Data under the old framework have been published since 2012, and can be found in the supplementary data tables of the relevant police workforce publications via the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales</a></p><p> </p><p>Any comparisons at force level should be made with care due to collaboration arrangements between forces for particular functions. Additionally, police functions data are often affected by re-structuring within police forces. Therefore comparisons over time for specific functions should be made with care.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-07-24T12:23:41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752161/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752161/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-14","Counter-terrorism: Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many police officers were assigned to counter-terrorism duties in (a) 2011 and (b) 2016.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","4996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752162","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-20","<p>We wrote on 22 June and 11 July to update all Members of Parliament on the Grenfell Tower disaster, and will continue to provide regular updates at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/grenfell-tower" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/grenfell-tower</a></p><p>We, as well as Home Office colleagues, will continue to provide what information we can to hon. Members during the public inquiry.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-20T14:32:50.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752162/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752162/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-14","Grenfell Tower Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will continue to answer questions from hon. Members on fire safety in high-rise towers during the public inquiry into the Grenfell Tower fire incident.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","5062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752163","Department of Health","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Government has not made a year on year estimate of the number of additional nurse training places that will be available up to 2020; Health Education England (HEE) produces a workforce plan on an annual basis which sets out the estimated minimum requirements for the National Health Service to meet the longer-term NHS workforce needs.</p><p> </p><p>Pre-registration nurse training places will no longer be commissioned in the same way that has been done previously by HEE. The reforms for healthcare education funding mean students will move onto the student loans system; giving universities the flexibility to provide additional places, based on local need and NHS clinical capacity. HEE will continue to fund the required number of clinical placements to meet the longer-term NHS workforce needs.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-07-19T14:34:53.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752163/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752163/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-14","Nurses: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 5 July 2017 to Question 2280 on nurses: training, what estimate his Department has made of the number of additional nursing training places that will be available for each year until 2020.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","4998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752164","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Department does not separately track the cost of sanctioning and monitoring claimants. A decision to sanction a claimant forms only part of a number of different roles including monitoring and supporting into work and we do not separate the cost of those roles into sanction and non-sanction activity. Therefore we cannot provide a definitive cost for these activities for the last six months.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-19T16:25:52.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752164/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752164/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-14","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 11 July 2017 to Question 3252, how much his Department has spent (a) sanctioning and (b) monitoring benefit claimants in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","5032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752165","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-19","<p>Plans to reinforce the South Atlantic Islands should an emergency situation arise are robust.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-19T14:58:55.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752165/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/752165/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-14","Falkland Islands: Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of his Department's ability to reinforce the Falkland Islands in an emergency after the rerouting of the South Atlantic air bridge.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","5033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751652","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Chancellor receives representations from a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery. Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-18T14:55:06.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751652/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751652/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-13","Taxation: Hearing Impairment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has received from organisations representing sign-language interpreters for the deaf on the IR35 tax system.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","4767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751653","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>There was a one off Banker’s Bonus Tax in 2009-10 aimed at encouraging banks to rebuild their financial base in the wake of the financial crisis.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010, the government has been clear that banks should make a fair contribution to the Exchequer. For that reason, in 2011 the government introduced the bank levy, a tax on banks’ balance sheets that has so far raised £14.3bn. In 2015 the government set out a long term plan for bank taxation, announcing the introduction of an 8% bank corporation tax surcharge alongside reform of the levy. The OBR forecast that these two measures will raise £18.9bn over the next five years.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4784","2017-07-18T14:59:21.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751653/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751653/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751653/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-13","Bank Levy","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the annual yield to the Exchequer of reversing the rate reduction of the Bank Levy introduced in 2015.","false","Biography information for Stewart Hosie","Dundee East","Stewart Hosie","4783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751654","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>There was a one off Banker’s Bonus Tax in 2009-10 aimed at encouraging banks to rebuild their financial base in the wake of the financial crisis.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010, the government has been clear that banks should make a fair contribution to the Exchequer. For that reason, in 2011 the government introduced the bank levy, a tax on banks’ balance sheets that has so far raised £14.3bn. In 2015 the government set out a long term plan for bank taxation, announcing the introduction of an 8% bank corporation tax surcharge alongside reform of the levy. The OBR forecast that these two measures will raise £18.9bn over the next five years.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4783","2017-07-18T14:59:21.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751654/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751654/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751654/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-13","Banks: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the annual yield to the Exchequer of the introduction of a banker's bonus tax.","false","Biography information for Stewart Hosie","Dundee East","Stewart Hosie","4784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751655","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has stringent governance arrangements in place where insolvency is considered. Each case is considered individually and, where a company is trading insolvent, HMRC must take the most appropriate action to mitigate the tax losses. Many factors are considered when deciding whether to petition against a company.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC treats unpaid Accelerated Payments as any other established debt using their range of debt collection powers as necessary to recover what is owed, including insolvency powers where appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC does not hold information on the amount recovered from company liquidations caused by unpaid accelerated payment notice debts. Any insolvency action in relation to unpaid accelerated payment notices is currently at an early stage.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4787","2017-07-18T15:03:38.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751655/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751655/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751655/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-13","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much HM Revenue and Customs has recovered from company liquidations caused by unpaid accelerated payment notice debts.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","4786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751656","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>The government has committed to review the exemption for milk-based products in 2020 based on evidence from Public Health England on the progress the industry has made on reformulating their products.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-07-18T14:52:46.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751656/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751656/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751656/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-13","Soft Drinks: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of extending the Soft Drinks Industry Levy to include milk-based products.","false","Biography information for Stewart Hosie","Dundee East","Stewart Hosie","4785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751657","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-20","<p>Earlier this year, the Government gave councils access to £9.25 billion more dedicated funding for social care over the next three years. This includes an additional £2 billion of funding in England, as announced at the Spring Budget 2017. The appropriate staffing required by a council to meet their duties is a matter for local authorities to determine.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-07-20T14:16:19.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751657/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751657/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751657/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-13","Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the (a) financial capacity and (b) staffing resources of local councils to discharge their statutory social care duties effectively in 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","4806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751658","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-20","<p>The Department for Communities and Local Government does not have a direct role nor does it provide funding in respect of measures to protect religious buildings from attack. The Jewish Community Protective Security Grant, the Places of Worship security funding scheme and the Vulnerable Faith Institutions scheme are the responsibility of the Home Office.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-07-20T14:11:15.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751658/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751658/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-13","Religious Buildings: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department (a) has a role and (b) provides funding in respect of Government measures to protect religious buildings from attack.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","4808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751659","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-20","<p>It is too early to make long-term decisions about what should happen with the site, which is a matter for the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea local authority to determine having consulted with survivors, relatives of those who lost their lives and the wider community. We understand the sensitivity and strong emotions, and will work with Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea local authority to ensure that their discussions are open and inclusive.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-20T15:00:58.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751659/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751659/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751659/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751659/answer/previousversion/5620","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-13","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to ensure that the site of Grenfell Tower becomes a memorial garden in perpetuity commemorating the people who lost their life in the Grenfell Tower fire, the survivors and those who saved them.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","4765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751660","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-18","<p>There are currently around 125 Armed Forces personnel based in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, delivering the breadth of UK defence engagement with Saudi Arabia. Amongst their many tasks, these personnel deliver training, which we assess helps develop the Saudi-led Coalition's targeting processes and supports their compliance with International Humanitarian Law. During courses, additional personnel either deploy to Saudi Arabia, or provide training in the UK.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-18T16:28:27.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751660/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751660/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751660/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-13","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK armed forces personnel are currently involved in training operations in support of aerial targeting procedures used by the airforces of Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","4768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751661","Department for Education","false","2017-07-24","<p>The department has no framework of its own for assessing value for money; instead it follows the framework set out by HM Treasury in the Green Book, “appraisal and evaluation in central government”.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-07-24T15:27:56.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751661/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751661/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-13","Department For Education: Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will publish the value-for-money framework which her Department applies to all private finance 2 projects.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","4764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751662","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Saudi-led Coalition Joint Incidents Assessment Team (JIAT) has announced the findings of a total of 21 investigations, with the most recent announced on 2 April 2017.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-07-18T16:02:15.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751662/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751662/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-13","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many responses from the Joint Incident Assessment Team to incidents in Yemen referred to it by the Government he has received in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","4766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751663","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>We are concerned by the recent arrests of Amnesty staff in Turkey, and the Prime Minister raised the case of Idil Eser with President Erdogan at the recent G20 summit. We continue to encourage Turkey to work towards the full protection of fundamental rights, particularly in the area of freedom of expression.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-07-18T16:22:27.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751663/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751663/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-07-13","Idil Eser","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has made representations to the Turkish Government on the detention of Idil Eser, the Director of Amnesty International, in that country.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","4772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751664","Department of Health","false","2017-07-18","<p>On Tuesday 11 July, the Prime Minister announced the intention to hold an inquiry into the events that surrounded the infection of thousands of people with HIV and/or hepatitis C through National Health Service supplied blood or blood products.</p><p> </p><p>The Welsh Government will be consulted as the Inquiry is taken forward.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-07-18T16:01:39.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751664/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751664/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-13","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what meetings (a) he, (b) Ministers of his Department and (c) officials of his Department have had with counterparts in the Welsh Government on the terms of the recently announced inquiry into contaminated blood.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","4769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751665","Department of Health","false","2017-07-18","<p>The methodology after the Outline Business Case stage for assessing value for money for schemes which are to be conventionally funded, is then unchanged from existing guidance in e.g. the Capital Investment Manual, published in 1994.</p><p> </p><p>In November 2011 the Coalition Government announced a complete reform of the Private Finance Initiative (PFI) model after a review. This recognised the need to address the widespread concerns with PFI – too slow and expensive; too inflexible and a lack of transparency. A new Public Private Partnership model to replace the PFI was announced in 2012, Private Finance 2 (PF2). Key features of the new PF2 model include the Government co-investing in projects as a minority shareholder to strengthen the partnership working and share in any returns and exclusion of 'soft' facilities management services such as cleaning and catering to improve flexibility.</p><p> </p><p>As part of the PFI review, the Coalition Government undertook to revise the value for money guidance. Further guidance was published in December 2012.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-07-18T16:02:45.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751665/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751665/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-13","Department of Health: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will publish the value-for-money framework which his Department applies to all non private finance 2 and private finance 1 projects.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","4763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751666","Home Office","false","2017-07-18","<p>Decisions on how the police enforce the law and deploy their available resources, including collaboration arrangements, are the responsibility of individual Chief Officers, taking into account the specific local problems and demands with which they are faced.</p><p>The Home Office has therefore not made any assessment of the effect of the withdrawal of West Mercia Police from the Central Motorway Police Group (CMPG) on levels of public safety.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","4774","2017-07-18T12:45:06.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751666/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751666/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-13","Central Motoring Police Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of the decision of West Mercia Police to withdraw from the Central Motorway Police Group on its responsibility to collaborate effectively with other police forces.","false","Biography information for Jack Dromey","Birmingham, Erdington","Jack Dromey","4773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751667","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-07-18","<p>I would be pleased to meet the hon. Members for Houghton and Sunderland South and Sunderland Central to discuss the future of the court estate in Sunderland. I will ask my office to make appropriate arrangements.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-07-18T16:33:59.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751667/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751667/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-07-13","Courts: Sunderland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will meet the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland and the hon. Member for Sunderland Central to discuss the future of the Sunderland Court Estate.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","4771"
